        },
        "Description": {
          "en": {
            "Spans": [
              {
                "Text": "A root is the portion of a word that (i) is common to a set of derived or inflected forms, if any, when all affixes are removed, (ii) is not further analyzable into meaningful elements, being morphologically simple, and, (iii) carries the principal portion of meaning of the words in which it functions.",
